
Williamsburg, 29 Mch. 1780. Appointment to command the detachment of Virginia troops, consisting of volunteers of the State Garrison Regiment, The greater part of Marshalls Corps of Artillery and two Troops of Nelsons horse, to be under Porterfields absolute controul and Command and to be prepared to march on the Shortest notice to [338] Charleston, S.C.; also instructions for procedure. Signed by Innes and Lyne. Countersigned: In Council Apl. 6th. 1780. Approved. Th: Jefferson.
